<strong>Mustang Membership - $7,000 (Maximum 10 Companies): </strong>One selected representative will be assigned to join the council and is eligible to be elected to the Board of Directors. This individual will be appreciated, and their organization will be invited to participate in the following Mustang Level opportunities:
<ol>
 	<li>Two CM career fairs (Fall and Winter) with Priority Registration1</li>
 	<li>Two departmental recruitment sessions (one info session and one Meet &amp; Greet) with Priority Registration1</li>
 	<li>Two seats at CMAC general meetings</li>
 	<li>Two seats at the Sigma Lambda Chi dinner</li>
 	<li>Invitation to CMAC Mixers</li>
 	<li>Opportunity to participate in the Carpenter’s Apprenticeship Program</li>
 	<li>Opportunity to partner with the CM Department for the Diversity and Inclusion Initiatives</li>
 	<li>Opportunity to partner with the CM Department for the Student Engagement Programs</li>
 	<li>Opportunity to reserve two interview rooms</li>
 	<li>Company logo in the interview room</li>
 	<li>Company logo at the CCCE website (ccce.calpoly.edu)</li>
 	<li>Company literature in the main recruiting room2</li>
 	<li>Opportunity to host CMAC Mixers</li>
</ol>
<strong>Gold Membership - $5,000 (Maximum 30 companies): </strong>One selected representative will be assigned to join the council and is eligible to be elected to the Board of Directors. This individual will be appreciated, and their organization will be invited to participate in the following Gold Level opportunities:
<ol>
 	<li>Two CM career fairs (Fall and Winter) with Priority Registration1</li>
 	<li>One departmental recruitment session (info session) with Priority Registration1</li>
 	<li>One seat at CMAC general meetings</li>
 	<li>Invitation to CMAC Mixers</li>
 	<li>Opportunity to participate in the Carpenter’s Apprenticeship Program</li>
 	<li>Opportunity to partner with the CM Department for the Diversity and Inclusion Initiatives</li>
 	<li>Opportunity to partner with the CM Department for the Student Engagement Programs</li>
 	<li>Company logo at the CCCE website (ccce.calpoly.edu)</li>
</ol>
<strong>Green Membership - $3,000 (Maximum 20 companies): </strong>One selected representative will be assigned to join the council and is eligible to be elected to the Board of Directors. This individual will be appreciated, and their organization will be invited to participate in the following Green Level opportunities:
<ol>
 	<li>Two CM career fairs (Fall and Winter) with Regular Registration</li>
 	<li>A seat at CMAC general meetings</li>
 	<li>Opportunity to participate in the Carpenter’s Apprenticeship Program</li>
 	<li>Opportunity to partner with the CM Department for the Diversity and Inclusion Initiatives</li>
 	<li>Opportunity to partner with the CM Department for the Student Engagement Programs</li>
 	<li>Invitation to CMAC Mixers</li>
 	<li>Company logo at the CCCE website (ccce.calpoly.edu)</li>
</ol>
<strong style="color: #000000; font-family: OpenSans-Regular;">Individual Membership - $200: </strong>Any individual and Construction Management alumni interested in being part of the advisory council
<ol>
 	<li><span style="color: #333333; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', 'Bitstream Charter', Times, serif;">Eligible to be elected to the Board of Directors</span></li>
 	<li>Invitation to CMAC Mixers</li>
 	<li>One seats at CMAC general meetings</li>
 	<li>Annual <u>Construction Innovator</u> magazine free of charge</li>
 	<li>Exclusive LinkedIn networking group</li>
</ol>
<ul></ul>
► Current Construction Management graduates will receive one year of free membership
<h6>1 Priority Registration – It allows to register early so eligible partners can get a preferred date of the recruiting sessions before they fill up. To be eligible, companies must participate in the Mustang or Gold level partnership.</h6>
<h6>2 Construction Innovations Center Room B202</h6>
